  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Winterization assistance for vulnerable drought IDPs in Badghis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With thousands of drought displaced households currently exposed to increasingly harsh winter conditions, IRC is proposing to provide a half package of winterization assistance to 3765 vulnerable households to support them in having access to fuel for the winter. IRC has coordinated with other ES/NFI partners to ensure duplication is avoided, and assistance gaps are filled for vulnerable households. The proposed intervention will represent a scale-up of the ongoing IRC response in the target displacement sites, as IRC is already conducting programming with emergency shelter and cash for NFIs, and will be starting protection and multi-purpose cash assistance. 
At present, there are scarce resources for winterization despite predictions of a harsh winter, and high vulnerabilities across much of the country which have been exacerbated due to the drought. Through the requested resources, IRC will provide support for covering winterization gaps to 3765 drought displaced households for heating materials, in order to reduce morbidity and mortality during the winter months, for those that are unable to return. 
In addition, ES/NFI partners are working alongside UNHCR to distribute tents to fill the emergency shelter gaps for drought IDPs. IRC will support a shelter gap of 12 tents in the target area, as determined through coordination of the IDP sites with other ES/NFI partners.
All assistance provision will be closely coordinated with other implementing partners and relevant government focal points. Additionally, coordination will take place with all relevant cluster implementing partners (FSAC, WASH, protection etc.) such that target households will be able to receive as holistic an assistance package as possible.</narrative>
  </description>
